# This is the factory repo (harness-loom). The patterns below cover artifacts
# the factory also produces when it is **self-installed** as its own target —
# running `/harness-init .` here regenerates these locally without polluting
# commits.

# Derived platform trees — produced by `node .harness/loom/sync.ts` from
# canonical `.harness/loom/` staging. Always regenerable; never committed.
.claude/
.codex/
.gemini/

# Runtime workspace for self-install: `.harness/loom/` is canonical staging,
# `.harness/cycle/` mutates per orchestrator turn, and `.harness/_archive/`
# holds past cycles that the orchestrator moves there on a goal-different
# reset. Out-of-cycle artifacts the cycle-end Finalizer produces land at the
# target root (`docs/`, `*.md`) — not under `.harness/` — and are committed
# to the target repo, not ignored there.
# None of the `.harness/` paths should land in factory commits.
.harness/

# Pointer docs the factory tracks as source-of-truth (authored by humans). They
# are listed here so that a Finalizer write from a self-install run does NOT
# silently overwrite the committed version; the committed files stay tracked
# because git keeps previously-tracked paths even when gitignored.
CLAUDE.md
AGENTS.md

# Ephemeral goal markdown fed to `/harness-orchestrate <goal.md>` during
# factory self-testing. Rewritten per cycle; never part of the repo history.
goals.md
